This paper is likely to belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category as it discusses the design of a wearable health monitoring platform that aims to improve clinical care for movement disorders. The paper also touches on technical challenges that hinder the widespread adoption of wearable devices, which could fall under the Cybersecurity (cs.CY) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of machine learning algorithms for human activity and gesture recognition, which could fall under the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Finally, the paper's title includes the phrase "Open Source," which could suggest that it belongs to the Open Science (cs.OH) sub-category.
